#3. ppa repositories
ppa stands personal package archives where software vendors or an individual can deliver their early versions/beta to the world directly before those got approved by ubuntu to get into official repository

The ubuntu has provded an https://launchpad.net/ubuntu/
where people can register and create repository and publish their software packages to the world.
	
How to install the software package from the ppa repository of the ubuntu?
1. We need to add the ppa repository into the /etc/apt/sources.list file as a ppa repository using the below command
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:repositoryName

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:ansible/ansible

2. refresh the cache
sudo apt update

3. then we can install the ppa package by looking at its name
sudo apt search packageName
sudo apt install packageName
